		    XPCE Development Licence summary
		    ================================

This licence sheet belongs to the XPCE/SWI-Prolog development system and
summarises your rights.

Copyrights
==========

XPCE is NOT PUBLIC DOMAIN, NOR COPY-LEFT.   A licence can be obtained by
writing or E-mailing to xpce-request@swi.psy.uva.nl.   This  software is
owned by:

	Dept. of Social Science Informatics (SWI)
	University of Amsterdam
	Roetersstraat 15
	1018 WB  Amsterdam
	The Netherlands


Licenced User
=============

Your are licenced to use this software if   you  have a copy of the XPCE
licence sheet signed by the University of Amsterdam or you are using the
binary-only demonstration version for PC/Linux.


Redistribution of this software
===============================

You are not allowed to redistribute any part of this software, except as
part of the RUNTIME system as  described   in  the file RT-LICENCE. Note
that the XPCE and Prolog  binaries  need   to  be  compiled as a runtime
(-DO_RUNTIME) system in this case.

You are allowed to redistribute   the  binary-only demonstration version
for PC/Linux of this software, provided you  make no modifications to it
and donot charge more that reasonable   handling costs for packaging and
distribution.

